title: View of the Ocean and Cliffs with Possible Shrine on Path
provenance: Anna Richards Brewster, Scarsdale, NY,1905-1952; William T. Brewster,
medium: Pen and black ink on off-white wove paper
description: Large craggy cliff in right foreground wwith road twisting around it and out of view, and a (possible) shrine structure. Below and in the distance, choppy ocean out to horizon. Dramatic, cloudy sky.
